                    "company": "University of Zurich",
                    "description": "In this project, I designed a cosmic emulator of the large scale structure power spectrum that will be used by the EUCLID mission to constrain multiple cosmological parameters such as the Hubble constant, teh matter and dark matter density parameters and the spectral index of the power spectrum of primordial matter fluctuations. I used three codes : CLASS (C) to compute the linear matter power spectrum, the N-body simulation PKDGRAV (C) to compute the non-linear power spectrum and the UQLab (Matlab) the framework for uncertainty quantification to build the cosmic emulator. The emulator is able to compute a boost factor (ratio between the power spectra in the linear and non-linear regime) for a wide variety of parameters at a very low computational cost. In addition, I also improved the PKDGRAV code by including the relativistic background.",
