                    "description": "Hexavalent chromium is a chemical used in the coating of planes to prevent rust but its use has been prohibited in 2017 due to being carcinogenic. Hence, the group Safran explored multiple ways to replace Chrome VI as a coating. The new material needs to protect the plane against corrosion and conduct electricity  to ensure the safety of passengers in case of lightnings. \nMy job was to provide of proof of concept and evaluate the number of silver nanowires to insert in a neutral anti-corrosion coating to turn it into a conductive material through percolation. As too many wires would both be expensive and reduce the anti-rust properties, I needed to find the minimum number of wires to add while also exploring the importance of the size and width of the nanowires. The project lead to the development of a new coating used for planes.",
